# Dev server — no manual restart

- **Never** ask the user to restart the dev server manually (`npm run dev`, "starta om servern", etc.).
- The **dev-runtime** agent keeps the app running via `dev:watch` (`npm run dev:start:ai` in worktree `home-pantry-dev`).

## After these changes, keep working

When you edit:

- `.env` / `.env.example`
- `src/hooks.server.ts`
- `src/lib/infrastructure/db/**`

Do **not** instruct a manual restart. Assume the dev-runtime watcher restarts automatically. Continue with your task (tests, code, commits).

Only mention server issues if something is clearly broken (e.g. port conflict, crash on boot) — then describe the error, not "please restart dev".
